						               													<description>Almighty: a Game of Gods &amp;amp; Ends is a competitive game of divine proportions. You are a primordial cosmic deity: control a pantheon of gods and act upon your many followers in all the ways that ancient deities tend to do: create stuff, destroy stuff, make mysterious omens and increasingly outrageous demands&amp;mdash;all to generate the divine power needed to perform greater acts, attract greater followers, and prove once and for all that YOU are the almightiest in the universe!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Almighty is a worker placement, hand management and tableau building game. Each turn, players will choose an Act card from their tableau, assign a matching God from their Pantheon to perform it, and play one or more Followers from hand to impact. Acts and Followers generate Boons such as Belief (used to buy better Acts and new Gods from an open market), Power (needed at increasingly higher levels to perform better Acts), more Followers, or Souls (which can be spent on bonus actions, but grant victory points if left in your Underworld).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is broken into several Ages, during which players will compete to perform the most Acts in a certain category (like Creation, Destruction, Omens, etc) to win the pot of Offering bonuses that accumulate each round. Players also have secret Prophecy cards that grant further victory points if achieved by the End of Days&amp;mdash;the final, apocalyptic doomsday round of the game in which the main restrictions are lifted to allow every player to do their Almighty Best to make their mark on the universe. The player with the most points at the end wins the title of ALMIGHTY!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
